choices.text:
to:

walk there

Walk up hill

Walk down hill

Teach during the walk

Ask for directions on the way

Run up hill / run down hill

Bike or scooter up hill

Bike or scooter down hill

Buy drugs across the highway

Grab someone’s scooter handle to stop them from getting away if the conversation goes bad

Climb a pole to steal coconuts

Learn how to climb poles like a Buddhist monk

Drink a glass of water

Book a yoga retreat

Douse a burning fire with water

Take out the batteries from things

Find a new place to get free wifi

Take out and put in earplugs

Eat a popsicle

Rain a little

Get the hang of being in the rain

Wash some dishes

Watch a YouTube video

Stop wearing hearing protection while doing nothing

Go to bed knowing a plan is in place and will be remembered come the next morning

Just breathe

Being on the road is easy. Travelling with the illness is difficult. But being able to stick to our plan, despite the illness, is worth gold.
